{"id": 7, "category": "data_integrity", "description": "Numeric coercion in `_python_value` converts any Decimal whose value equals its integer truncation to `int`, but any other Decimal is cast to `float`. Monetary aggregates like `SUM(PNL_SUM)` can produce Decimals with many digits; float casting drops precision beyond ~15 significant digits, silently distorting reported rubles for large totals.", "code_ref": "ai_analyst/db.py:66-73", "reproducer": "import decimal; from ai_analyst.db import _python_value; _python_value(decimal.Decimal('12345678901234.56789')) → 12345678901234.568 (lost digits)", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 8, "category": "error_handling", "description": "OracleClient.execute opens a cursor but never issues `rollback()` on exception; oracledb keeps an implicit transaction state after a failed statement. For a single-shot CLI this is mostly cosmetic, but on retry within the same agent run a failed DDL-looking query can leave the connection in a state that breaks subsequent SELECTs with ORA-01453-style errors.", "code_ref": "ai_analyst/db.py:135-148", "reproducer": "Inspection only — no explicit transaction handling around cursor.execute.", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "speculative"}
{"id": 9, "category": "correctness", "description": "Tool result column lookup is case-blind via `c.upper()`, but Oracle preserves case for quoted identifiers and oracledb returns column names exactly as Oracle emits them. If the LLM uses a double-quoted lowercase alias (e.g. `SUM(PNL_SUM) AS \"income\"`), the column comes back lower-case while the agent's `non_null_columns:['income']` works, but a quoted mixed-case alias plus user-provided expectation in different case will mismatch and report 'колонка не найдена'.", "code_ref": "ai_analyst/tools.py:129-150", "reproducer": "Edge case: quoted alias `\"Income\"` returns column 'Income'; expectation 'income' uppercases to 'INCOME' which never matches.", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 10, "category": "error_handling", "description": "Agent loop has no recovery for empty/whitespace LLM output without tool_calls beyond appending one nudge message. If the local Ollama model habitually returns empty content without tool_calls (common for smaller quantized chat models), the loop will burn all `max_steps` then raise `RuntimeError('Агент не сошёлся за N шагов')` — the CLI converts this to exit code 1 and no useful answer, even when the question was trivial.", "code_ref": "ai_analyst/agent.py:96-112,162-166", "reproducer": "Patch LLM to always return empty content + no tool_calls → after 12 steps RuntimeError.", "severity": "major", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 11, "category": "security", "description": "Read-only firewall is pure-regex over the SQL string and can be bypassed via Oracle constructs the blacklist doesn't enumerate. Examples: hierarchical/recursive CONNECT BY with FUNCTION calls, `SELECT ... FROM TABLE(DBMS_XMLGEN.getxml('...'))`, DBMS_LOB/DBMS_SCHEDULER side-effect-capable PL/SQL packages invoked via SELECT, autonomous function objects. None of `dbms_*`, `lock`, `xmltype`, `sys.`, hidden hint-side-channels appear in `_FORBIDDEN_PATTERNS`.", "code_ref": "ai_analyst/db.py:21-23", "reproducer": "assert_readonly_sql(\"SELECT DBMS_LOB.SUBSTR(some_lob,1,1) FROM dual\") → passes silently; SELECT * FROM TABLE(DBMS_XPLAN.DISPLAY) → passes.", "severity": "major", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 12, "category": "missing_feature", "description": "OracleClient passes no character-set / NLS settings. With oracledb thin mode the client defaults rely on environment; Cyrillic values (ORGANIZATION_NM, GROUP_NM) and Cyrillic literals in SQL (`LIKE '%Лукойл%'`) can come back as mojibake/`?` if the DB charset is not AL32UTF8 or the client is misconfigured, silently producing wrong matches.", "code_ref": "ai_analyst/db.py:110-117", "reproducer": "No call to `oracledb.defaults.config_dir` or explicit `encoding`/`nencoding`; no `os.environ['NLS_LANG']` setup.", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "speculative"}
